          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a manual used by priests for making water libations in honor of the primordial sages (ṛṣis). Manuscript is a collection of some of the offerings mentioned in the larger work and includes the Kātīyasnānavidhi and Yajñapavītasaṃskāra. The front page contains twenty-five mantras dedicated to the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa (f. 1r).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Ṛṣitarpaṇa</title>
              <title type="vernacular">ऋषितर्पण</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti maṃtreṇa yajñopavītagraṃthiṃ kuryāt / dakṣiṇahastena spṛśet / tatodaśa[kṛ]tvasāvivyāmaṃtritārāpaḥ miraṭbhiḥ saṃvet / savaṃsaṃskṛtaṃ yajñopavītaṃ ṣārapet // (f. 25r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
